WEBVTT

00:00.174 --> 00:02.089
[Camille]
She wanted me to stay.

00:02.176 --> 00:03.394
And now she's dead.

00:03.525 --> 00:05.788
Throw this opportunistic
baggage out.

00:05.918 --> 00:06.876
[Majordome] A weapon should
be in the hands of someone

00:06.963 --> 00:08.486
who knows how to use it.

00:08.617 --> 00:11.141
I can't read it.
There's a water stain. Apri--

00:11.272 --> 00:13.665
-Apricot, perhaps.
-Your wife's words.

00:13.796 --> 00:16.146
She took her own life.
Because of you.

00:16.233 --> 00:19.541
Support her last wish,
that I flourish here in Paris,

00:19.671 --> 00:22.239
or I will share
your wife's ungodly act

00:22.370 --> 00:23.936
with all your society.

00:24.024 --> 00:25.155
Rose, let us pass.

00:25.286 --> 00:26.548
What will you give me?

00:28.898 --> 00:30.378
[Gabriel] There's no place
here for a man

00:30.508 --> 00:32.119
so lacking in morality.

00:32.249 --> 00:33.816
My father's title, his fortune,

00:33.903 --> 00:35.296
should have been mine
when he died,

00:35.426 --> 00:36.166
but you poisoned him
against me.

00:36.297 --> 00:37.776
My letters.

00:37.863 --> 00:39.604
Do you know how dangerous
it is to have them?

00:39.735 --> 00:41.780
Less dangerous than not
having them, I think.

00:41.867 --> 00:43.260
[Jean] How could you
possibly know a woman

00:43.347 --> 00:45.523
such as
Jacqueline de Montrachet?

00:45.654 --> 00:47.134
[Camille]
She promised me everything.

00:47.264 --> 00:49.658
Then she threw me away
as if I were nothing.

00:49.788 --> 00:53.401
[Geneviève] Avenge our sex.
Devise strategies.

00:53.488 --> 00:57.144
Conquer or die.

00:58.319 --> 01:01.104
[soft string music plays]

01:01.191 --> 01:03.846
♪ ♪

01:16.206 --> 01:17.207
[Pascal] Here you go.

01:22.038 --> 01:25.041
Monsieur. Food. Food for us.

01:37.140 --> 01:39.316
I think straight down
the middle is the fairest way.

01:52.460 --> 01:55.811
I made a new friend last night
at the opera.

01:55.941 --> 01:59.815
The Comtesse de l'Ancenis.
It will soon be like old times.

01:59.945 --> 02:01.382
[knock at door]

02:01.512 --> 02:03.166
Stay. Eat.

02:08.954 --> 02:11.740
[inquisitive music plays]

02:11.914 --> 02:14.264
♪ ♪

02:14.351 --> 02:16.832
[Azolan] What is it, sir?

02:16.919 --> 02:18.921
A fresh shirt, Azolan.

02:19.008 --> 02:21.402
It seems the Comtesse
awaits me.

02:21.532 --> 02:24.274
[dramatic string music plays]

02:24.448 --> 02:27.364
♪ ♪

03:25.117 --> 03:27.903
[lively string music plays]

03:27.990 --> 03:30.949
♪ ♪

03:54.799 --> 03:56.932
The Comtesse de l'Ancenis
is here already?

04:01.458 --> 04:03.808
I never discuss my patrons,
monsieur.

04:03.895 --> 04:05.854
That way, I keep them.

04:05.941 --> 04:08.857
♪ ♪

04:31.009 --> 04:34.274
Forgive me.
I have the wrong room.

04:34.404 --> 04:35.579
Did you ever look at me?

04:39.888 --> 04:43.631
To be fair, you rarely
had your clothes on.

04:43.761 --> 04:45.894
The card was from you. Why?

04:46.024 --> 04:48.070
You can't decide
between vermillion or cerise?

04:48.200 --> 04:50.855
You're starting
to look shabby, Valmont.

04:50.986 --> 04:53.031
I noticed at the opera.

04:53.118 --> 04:55.512
Perhaps now I'm surrounded
in all this finery,

04:55.643 --> 04:57.819
I notice the loose threads
about you, and it won't do.

04:57.906 --> 04:59.299
Didn't seem to trouble
my companion.

04:59.386 --> 05:03.172
I forget, you have
so many admirers.

05:03.303 --> 05:06.523
But that list grows shorter
by the day, I think.

05:06.654 --> 05:10.179
So everything you need
to look your best,

05:10.310 --> 05:12.007
courtesy of my guardian.

05:12.094 --> 05:14.139
New wardrobe
from Jean de Merteuil?

05:14.270 --> 05:16.664
No grief on earth
would compel him to generosity.

05:16.794 --> 05:18.666
Well, I've been encouraging
his charitable side.

05:18.796 --> 05:20.015
And do I want to know how?

05:21.843 --> 05:23.279
Undress for me.

05:23.410 --> 05:24.628
Ask me nicely.

05:24.759 --> 05:26.848
You are fortunate I ask at all.
Undress.

05:26.978 --> 05:27.849
[cane thumps]

05:30.330 --> 05:33.550
[suggestive string music plays]

05:33.724 --> 05:36.553
♪ ♪

05:48.304 --> 05:50.480
Put it on.

05:50.611 --> 05:51.829
Pussycat.

05:51.960 --> 05:53.309
Do not call me that.

06:00.664 --> 06:03.624
What would you give
to have me back?

06:03.754 --> 06:05.408
Everything.

06:10.370 --> 06:12.633
I am afraid to risk
so much for you.

06:15.984 --> 06:20.380
My place in Saint-Honoré,
the wardship of a marquis.

06:23.034 --> 06:25.385
I would have to be so sure
of you in deeds, not words.

06:25.515 --> 06:26.734
Tell me what to do.

06:29.258 --> 06:30.651
Anything?

06:37.658 --> 06:40.400
I would need to know
you understand what love means.

06:40.530 --> 06:42.314
What it takes.

06:44.447 --> 06:47.450
There is a woman in Paris.

06:47.581 --> 06:53.195
If you could seduce her,
not just in body, but in mind...

06:55.719 --> 06:57.112
...that might show me

06:57.199 --> 06:59.027
you're capable
of understanding love.

06:59.157 --> 07:00.985
Why not simply
make you love me?

07:04.380 --> 07:05.337
You did.

07:13.084 --> 07:14.825
Now you must be beyond doubt.

07:18.786 --> 07:21.528
Or I can never give myself
to you again.

07:21.615 --> 07:24.487
And there must be proof,
a letter, from her to you.

07:26.402 --> 07:29.231
Declaring her love.

07:29.318 --> 07:30.754
Isn't that your specialty?

07:41.417 --> 07:44.594
-Who is she?
-[Camille] Your challenge.

07:44.681 --> 07:46.422
Jacqueline de Montrachet.

07:49.294 --> 07:50.818
Tell Jean to prepare
the guestroom.

07:50.948 --> 07:53.777
I'll have you back
before the day is out.

07:53.908 --> 07:56.084
Send word when you have
made progress.

07:56.171 --> 07:58.739
♪ ♪

08:08.009 --> 08:09.184
Hiya!

08:12.666 --> 08:15.495
Don't look so disapproving.

08:15.625 --> 08:18.323
I derive no pleasure from him.

08:18.454 --> 08:20.412
I preferred you
as a whore than a liar.

08:33.164 --> 08:35.079
You forget my sweet tooth.

09:00.278 --> 09:01.889
Look what you do.

09:02.019 --> 09:02.890
Where is your head?

09:05.370 --> 09:06.371
Clean up your mess.

09:08.025 --> 09:11.420
And then, Majordome,
you must make your choice.

09:11.507 --> 09:15.337
You must decide to whom
in this house you are loyal.

09:15.467 --> 09:18.122
Bring me the letter my wife
intended for me.

09:22.562 --> 09:24.172
And remove that sash.

09:26.130 --> 09:28.002
This house is no longer
in mourning.

09:29.525 --> 09:32.528
[operatic vocalizing]

09:32.659 --> 09:35.313
[lively harpsichord music
plays]

09:35.487 --> 09:38.447
♪ ♪

09:41.189 --> 09:43.104
♪ My secret being mastery ♪

09:43.191 --> 09:47.021
♪ And being untouched ♪

09:47.151 --> 09:52.069
No, no, no! How many times?

09:52.156 --> 09:55.420
I must truly,
truly believe you as Daphne

09:55.507 --> 09:57.727
when you say you are a virgin.

09:57.814 --> 09:59.468
Quite frankly,
listening to that,

09:59.599 --> 10:01.165
I think I'd fucked you myself.

10:01.252 --> 10:02.384
But you have.

10:02.514 --> 10:05.953
I was speaking metaphorically.

10:06.083 --> 10:10.218
Go again, but this time,
molto, molto innocente!

10:10.305 --> 10:12.699
Every day,
you change the score.

10:12.786 --> 10:15.789
My libretto. My character.

10:15.919 --> 10:18.313
This is not an opera!
It's a tragedy!

10:18.443 --> 10:20.445
It's a shame you can't bring
that level of drama

10:20.532 --> 10:21.969
to your performance, darling.

10:27.975 --> 10:30.847
Difficult day, Theo.

10:30.934 --> 10:32.980
Well, look at you.

10:33.110 --> 10:36.636
Valmont in the daytime.
Is it the apocalypse?

10:42.163 --> 10:43.512
I need a favor.

10:43.643 --> 10:45.688
I have an opera to prepare

10:45.775 --> 10:47.037
-for the queen.
-[Pascal] Mm-hmm.

10:47.168 --> 10:48.735
And opening night
fast approaching,

10:48.865 --> 10:51.085
and still no story.

10:51.172 --> 10:52.826
It's I who needs the favor.

10:52.956 --> 10:55.176
[Pascal] Don't they always say
write what you know?

10:55.306 --> 10:57.787
Paris is not ready
for that opera.

10:57.918 --> 10:59.310
Oh!

10:59.441 --> 11:02.139
[Theo]
Now, what is this favor?

11:02.270 --> 11:04.576
Need you to find someone.

11:04.707 --> 11:06.143
A woman.

11:06.274 --> 11:07.536
Did I not see you
with the Comtesse de l'Ancenis

11:07.623 --> 11:09.103
last night?

11:09.233 --> 11:11.105
-She's not enough?
-Oh, she's far too much.

11:11.192 --> 11:14.630
And comes as a pair
with her husband.

11:14.717 --> 11:16.284
Theo.

11:16.414 --> 11:18.895
You're a man in demand
at every fine cellar,

11:19.026 --> 11:22.638
-not to mention Versailles.
-[Theo] Mm.

11:22.769 --> 11:25.902
Where will I find
Jacqueline de Montrachet?

11:27.991 --> 11:29.819
Tell me you don't seek
to fuck her.

11:31.647 --> 11:33.388
Can't you find
something meaningful

11:33.518 --> 11:35.477
-to do with your life?
-[Pascal] Hmm.

11:35.607 --> 11:37.479
One day, when I don't
have rent to pay.

11:37.609 --> 11:40.961
Where will I find her?

11:41.091 --> 11:43.833
On her knees.
But don't get excited.

11:43.920 --> 11:45.705
It's the Church
of Saint-Sauveur

11:45.792 --> 11:47.184
she can't get enough of.

11:49.273 --> 11:51.536
I'll pray for your opera
whilst I am there.

11:51.667 --> 11:52.929
Theo.

12:01.721 --> 12:04.071
We are no longer in mourning?

12:04.201 --> 12:05.594
Apparently not.

12:10.381 --> 12:13.994
Ah, here she is!
Our visitor from Carcassonne.

12:14.124 --> 12:16.910
Oh, Camille.

12:17.040 --> 12:19.521
I feel as if
I know you already.

12:19.651 --> 12:22.654
Oh, what sorrow
you have endured!

12:22.742 --> 12:25.614
I can see it in the dullness
of your eyes and skin.

12:27.790 --> 12:29.749
I'm sorry, we haven't
been introduced.

12:29.836 --> 12:33.491
How remiss of me.
The Comtesse de Sevigny.

12:37.365 --> 12:39.106
We'll get to know each other
over dinner tonight,

12:39.236 --> 12:42.979
and we can remember
my cousin in every detail.

12:50.987 --> 12:53.903
Though Geneviève was not one
for gossip, it's implausible

12:54.034 --> 12:55.600
I wouldn't have heard
of this Camille.

12:55.687 --> 12:57.559
A fact you will
illuminate tonight.

12:57.689 --> 13:00.910
A shadow can only survive
in the dark.

13:01.041 --> 13:03.739
Why do you not simply
cast her out?

13:03.870 --> 13:05.045
Far better that she leave

13:05.175 --> 13:06.829
because
she cannot bear to stay.

13:11.051 --> 13:12.574
[both chuckle]

13:14.837 --> 13:16.796
How can there be
no trace of her?

13:20.800 --> 13:23.933
I mean, they were cousins,
so there must be some letters,

13:24.020 --> 13:25.369
a journal,
something I can glean

13:25.500 --> 13:26.849
some sense
or knowledge of her from.

13:26.936 --> 13:28.416
There's nothing here.

13:31.158 --> 13:33.813
-Madame wanted to protect me.
-[Victoire] From what?

13:33.900 --> 13:35.815
You overestimate
her affections for you.

13:38.121 --> 13:39.993
I can't be exposed tonight.

13:40.123 --> 13:42.996
Then we should leave.

13:43.126 --> 13:46.260
Not until Valmont
does what he promised.

13:46.390 --> 13:48.958
[suspenseful string music
plays]

13:49.045 --> 13:51.918
♪ ♪

13:53.920 --> 13:55.922
[indistinct preaching]

13:59.882 --> 14:02.972
-Madame de Montrachet.
-Huh?

14:03.103 --> 14:04.365
Direct me to Madame
de Montrachet.

14:04.452 --> 14:06.323
I have a message for her.

14:12.416 --> 14:19.032
Love thinks no evil.
Bears all things. Believes...

14:19.162 --> 14:21.643
Love sounds like a bore
at a party.

14:21.773 --> 14:23.558
[both chuckle]

14:27.040 --> 14:29.564
Forgive me, madame,

14:29.694 --> 14:31.958
but I was compelled
to come closer to you.

14:32.088 --> 14:33.176
Why?

14:38.138 --> 14:41.576
You have bewitched me.

14:41.663 --> 14:45.710
I felt your presence
the moment I entered here.

14:45.841 --> 14:48.278
Then God does indeed
hear my prayer.

14:51.412 --> 14:54.241
Might he hear them
even more clearly outside?

14:54.328 --> 14:57.287
[playful music plays]

14:57.461 --> 14:58.549
♪ ♪

14:58.636 --> 15:01.944
[panting]

15:02.075 --> 15:06.644
I shall be known at confession.

15:06.775 --> 15:09.691
Forgive me.

15:09.778 --> 15:13.042
I have never felt
such desire for a stranger.

15:13.173 --> 15:17.177
Perhaps it's because I leave
Paris tonight for America.

15:17.264 --> 15:18.656
I don't know when I'll be back.

15:18.743 --> 15:22.573
My dear boy, it was very nice.

15:22.660 --> 15:24.358
But I have to get back.

15:24.488 --> 15:27.578
The sermon's about
to get very fiery.

15:27.709 --> 15:31.974
Grant me something
more tangible than a memory.

15:32.061 --> 15:33.671
A letter, perhaps, so that

15:33.802 --> 15:35.673
I may read it on my journey,
relive our joy.

15:35.804 --> 15:37.937
If it means we say "adieu."

15:40.591 --> 15:42.724
Might you address me
as your beloved Valmont,

15:42.854 --> 15:44.595
in your words,
of course, Jacqueline.

15:44.726 --> 15:47.250
Jacqueline?

15:47.381 --> 15:48.382
De Montrachet?

15:48.512 --> 15:50.297
Montachet.

15:50.427 --> 15:52.212
No. Montrachet.

15:52.299 --> 15:55.519
Candice Montachet. And you are?

15:57.565 --> 16:01.961
Mistaken. Madame.

16:02.091 --> 16:03.049
Adieu.

16:36.908 --> 16:38.954
Vicomtesse de Valmont.

16:39.085 --> 16:40.869
Thank you for granting me
this audience.

16:41.000 --> 16:42.653
You're not here to arrest me?

16:45.091 --> 16:47.484
I've stolen the hearts
of so many, monsieur.

16:54.448 --> 16:56.798
Why would the Unit
of Moral Discipline

16:56.885 --> 16:58.539
seek an audience with me?

16:58.626 --> 17:00.541
To discuss your
late husband's son.

17:00.628 --> 17:02.804
Prévan.

17:02.934 --> 17:05.024
[Gabriel] Pascal Valmont.

17:07.113 --> 17:09.811
If you are here to ask me
to pay for his drinking debts

17:09.941 --> 17:11.943
or the father of some
foolish girl he seduced,

17:12.074 --> 17:14.033
your journey is a wasted one.

17:14.163 --> 17:18.341
That...man has no place
in my family.

17:18.428 --> 17:21.083
May I ask
why he is so regarded?

17:21.170 --> 17:25.914
Perhaps I wasn't clear.
He is not regarded at all.

17:26.001 --> 17:28.308
A man without morals
has no place in my family.

17:28.438 --> 17:29.657
A man without morals

17:29.787 --> 17:31.615
is a danger to society,
Vicomtesse.

17:31.746 --> 17:34.183
He is disinherited
and penniless.

17:34.270 --> 17:36.055
He's as dangerous
as a blind hen.

17:38.666 --> 17:41.408
Do not underestimate what
those with nothing will do.

17:44.715 --> 17:46.630
Then why do you not act?

17:50.330 --> 17:53.550
I require more than
my suspicion, Vicomtesse.

17:53.681 --> 17:55.030
I require proof.

17:56.858 --> 17:58.164
And with this proof?

18:00.514 --> 18:03.343
I will see him
in a prison cell.

18:03.473 --> 18:06.476
Then we must hope
such proof is found.

18:06.563 --> 18:09.523
[suspenseful music plays]

18:09.697 --> 18:12.569
♪ ♪

18:18.401 --> 18:20.534
Please, Majordome.

18:20.621 --> 18:23.145
I've helped you enough.
I owe you nothing more.

18:23.276 --> 18:27.367
I'm not asking you to break
some kind of sacred trust.

18:27.454 --> 18:30.631
Just tell me who this woman is.

18:30.761 --> 18:33.199
Their time together.
The affection between them.

18:33.329 --> 18:35.723
There is tarnish.
See it is removed.

18:35.810 --> 18:37.290
[servant] Majordome.

18:42.121 --> 18:43.861
Madame promised to guide me
through this world.

18:43.948 --> 18:45.515
I'm lost here without her.

18:45.646 --> 18:47.387
I can tell you about etiquette.

18:47.517 --> 18:50.955
Which knife to use at table.
But I cannot fabricate a life,

18:51.086 --> 18:53.306
nor will I compromise
myself further.

18:54.959 --> 18:56.700
And why should I?

18:56.831 --> 18:58.137
You are not
who you say you are.

19:01.792 --> 19:06.580
No one is who they say
they are, Majordome.

19:06.710 --> 19:10.192
Is that your name?
Or was it given?

19:10.323 --> 19:13.848
Because if it was given, then
you are who they say you are.

19:16.155 --> 19:18.113
I need your help.

19:18.244 --> 19:21.160
If I thrive, so will you.
That's a promise.

19:21.290 --> 19:23.292
And I have saved you
once already here.

19:25.251 --> 19:28.297
I am not in need of a savior
such as you, mademoiselle.

19:31.257 --> 19:33.346
Your instructions
for dinner are noted.

19:33.520 --> 19:36.349
♪ ♪

20:05.682 --> 20:06.683
[Majordome] Mademoiselle.

20:08.468 --> 20:11.384
You should pray more,
as madame did.

20:11.471 --> 20:13.734
You mock me now?

20:13.821 --> 20:15.823
It gave her guidance
when she needed it most,

20:15.910 --> 20:19.130
and you are a woman
in much need of guidance,

20:19.261 --> 20:22.656
not least in how
you address me in the future.

20:22.786 --> 20:26.268
Don't ever imagine
you know who I am.

20:38.889 --> 20:41.675
[singing in Italian]

20:41.762 --> 20:44.373
[lively harpsichord music
plays]

20:46.288 --> 20:48.551
[applause]

20:48.682 --> 20:51.728
I have abused your
music teacher long enough.

20:51.859 --> 20:53.991
Delight us
with your honeyed voice.

20:54.122 --> 20:56.429
Everybody, Camille is here.

20:56.516 --> 20:58.082
Camille.

21:05.089 --> 21:07.701
The Comte de Sevigny
and his daughter Emilie.

21:07.831 --> 21:08.919
[Emilie] Camille.[laughs]

21:11.139 --> 21:13.141
We will be like sisters
while I'm in Paris,

21:13.228 --> 21:14.621
especially as now I am

21:14.708 --> 21:17.537
no longer
a prisoner of the convent.

21:17.624 --> 21:18.973
The Chevalier d'Ancenis.

21:21.018 --> 21:22.411
And you've already met
the Comtesse.

21:28.635 --> 21:31.638
We look forward to learning
everything about you.

21:36.904 --> 21:37.731
[Majordome]
Dinner is served, Marquis.

21:37.818 --> 21:39.472
[Jean] At last.

21:39.602 --> 21:41.648
Draw comfort from the book
if your mistress will not.

21:44.694 --> 21:47.567
[inquisitive music plays]

21:47.654 --> 21:50.570
♪ ♪

21:55.226 --> 21:57.011
Forgive me, mademoiselle.

21:57.141 --> 22:00.057
You will find we're sticklers
for customs here, Camille.

22:04.975 --> 22:06.673
For your devotion, mistress.

22:11.852 --> 22:14.202
[Majordome] Christine
called madame "general,"

22:14.333 --> 22:16.335
a play on Geneviève.

22:16.465 --> 22:20.164
Madame in turn called her
"musket"--explosive

22:20.295 --> 22:21.818
and liable to go off
at any moment.

22:21.992 --> 22:24.604
♪ ♪

22:31.045 --> 22:35.092
To my late wife,
light of my darkness.

22:35.223 --> 22:37.007
We all feel your loss, Jean.

22:37.138 --> 22:39.053
None more so than I.

22:39.183 --> 22:42.404
Geneviève was to be
instrumental in our search

22:42.491 --> 22:44.624
for a match worthy of Emilie.

22:44.754 --> 22:48.062
With such a vast dowry,
I valued another pair of eyes.

22:48.149 --> 22:49.672
One can never have
too much scrutiny

22:49.759 --> 22:51.239
on the agenda of strangers.

22:51.326 --> 22:52.414
Well, I'm in no rush
to find a husband.

22:52.501 --> 22:54.721
[laughs] Nonsense, darling.

22:54.808 --> 22:56.418
The queen herself
will want to help.

22:56.505 --> 22:59.029
My wife is a favorite
of Her Majesty.

23:19.528 --> 23:21.835
Another little custom, Camille.

23:21.922 --> 23:25.621
But, uh, seeing as you are
so new to Paris,

23:25.708 --> 23:28.102
how did you come
to meet my cousin Geneviève?

23:35.805 --> 23:38.678
Perhaps first
a prayer of thanks.

23:38.808 --> 23:41.245
We're building
such anticipation.

23:46.250 --> 23:50.080
Our Lord Christ,
thou art here...

23:50.167 --> 23:53.083
[Majordome] Madame went
every spring alone to Geneva.

23:53.214 --> 23:54.955
The air and waters
were healing

23:55.085 --> 23:57.436
to the melancholic nature
she was disposed to.

23:57.566 --> 23:58.741
Amen.

23:58.828 --> 24:00.221
[all] Amen.

24:04.530 --> 24:08.534
My mother knew madame
from her time in Geneva.

24:08.664 --> 24:10.623
That is where I first met her.

24:13.060 --> 24:16.150
-Geneva?
-[Camille] Mm.

24:16.280 --> 24:18.761
Her melancholy always seemed
to lift when she was there.

24:18.848 --> 24:21.024
The melancholy
that plagued her.

24:21.155 --> 24:23.984
She would bathe in the lake
morning and night.

24:24.071 --> 24:26.726
As you know,
she couldn't abide the heat,

24:26.813 --> 24:30.643
but she would love the cool
of the water. [chuckles]

24:30.773 --> 24:33.776
I wish I did have more common
ground to share with you,

24:33.863 --> 24:36.039
but she rarely spoke of you.

24:36.170 --> 24:38.781
When she did, she--

24:38.912 --> 24:40.522
she called you "musket."

24:43.046 --> 24:46.659
I don't know why. Blessings.

24:49.879 --> 24:53.796
And yet your mother did not
come to pay her respects?

24:53.927 --> 24:57.452
The disadvantage
of her herself being dead.

24:59.976 --> 25:02.936
How I would adore to have heard
the conversations

25:03.023 --> 25:04.894
between you all.

25:05.025 --> 25:08.811
But Mama,
this is really--you can.

25:08.898 --> 25:10.813
We can ask
Geneviève herself.

25:10.944 --> 25:12.380
No more wine for you,
my darling.

25:12.467 --> 25:14.948
There's a man new to Paris,
a mesmerist.

25:15.078 --> 25:17.298
We heard about him at a
recital the other evening.

25:17.428 --> 25:19.256
[Emilie]
Crowds gather in the square,

25:19.387 --> 25:20.997
and he performs miracles.

25:21.128 --> 25:22.956
They say he receives messages
from the grave,

25:23.086 --> 25:25.175
that he can speak with ghosts.
He is...

25:25.306 --> 25:27.308
[both] Spectacular.

25:27.438 --> 25:29.005
And chilling.

25:32.661 --> 25:34.881
If he can commune with ghosts,

25:35.011 --> 25:37.971
might we not
invite him here, Jean?

25:38.101 --> 25:40.451
We could put your mind
at rest

25:40.582 --> 25:42.541
that Geneviève is at peace.

25:42.671 --> 25:44.934
[tense music plays]

25:45.065 --> 25:46.588
[scoffs]

25:46.719 --> 25:50.853
Your wife
had a deep faith, Marquis.

25:50.984 --> 25:53.334
A man such as that would be
at odds with her.

25:58.339 --> 26:00.950
If my wife has words for me,
I shall hear them.

26:01.081 --> 26:02.952
From whatever source they come.

26:04.911 --> 26:08.654
Then let him
bring back Geneviève.

26:08.784 --> 26:09.916
Blessings.

26:10.003 --> 26:12.875
♪ ♪

26:18.141 --> 26:20.970
Did you see her reaction
at the idea of a conduit

26:21.057 --> 26:24.931
for Geneviève?
She was terrified!

26:25.061 --> 26:26.933
One charlatan
in fear of another.

26:30.806 --> 26:34.941
But tell me you do not believe
that such things are possible.

26:35.071 --> 26:37.639
Where there is belief,
anything is possible.

26:39.641 --> 26:42.035
So let us...

26:42.122 --> 26:44.385
let us exploit her belief,

26:44.515 --> 26:46.082
and let Geneviève send her
packing

26:46.213 --> 26:51.566
from beyond the grave.

26:51.697 --> 26:55.526
You must not stay
in the dark alone, Jean,

26:55.657 --> 26:57.311
or more girls like this one

26:57.441 --> 26:59.313
will come to take advantage
of your good nature.

27:01.707 --> 27:02.577
Protect yourself.

27:05.232 --> 27:06.625
Find a new wife.

27:08.801 --> 27:10.629
One who will...

27:12.805 --> 27:16.635
...who will honor the great
title your name bestows.

27:25.818 --> 27:29.604
[Camille] "Well, Valmont,
have you succeeded?

27:29.691 --> 27:32.912
Do I make up the guest room?

27:33.042 --> 27:36.263
And I thought this challenge
would play to your strengths.

27:36.350 --> 27:38.178
Though perhaps
it is broken promises

27:38.265 --> 27:41.181
you are master of rather
than the hearts of women."

27:41.355 --> 27:44.314
♪ ♪

28:15.737 --> 28:18.566
[crowd murmuring indistinctly]

28:32.667 --> 28:34.713
[indistinct chatter]

28:37.237 --> 28:39.935
Stop. I know this one. Stop.

28:43.069 --> 28:44.287
Fetch Gabriel Carré.

28:47.769 --> 28:48.727
Get off.

28:51.642 --> 28:53.819
This way. Over here.

28:53.906 --> 28:56.778
♪ ♪

29:06.875 --> 29:09.573
I'm so sorry. It's her.

29:11.880 --> 29:12.925
It's Camille.

29:16.450 --> 29:18.104
She always wore it.

29:23.718 --> 29:25.981
See that no one touches her.

29:26.112 --> 29:27.678
If you're in need
of comfort--ah--

29:31.595 --> 29:32.771
[bell tolling]

29:32.901 --> 29:33.859
Cheers!

29:38.733 --> 29:40.561
She comes every morning
and night for communion,

29:40.691 --> 29:43.085
always dressed in white,
and always in a veil.

29:43.172 --> 29:44.783
They call her the ghost
around here,

29:44.913 --> 29:46.959
but apparently,
she's quite generous.

29:50.397 --> 29:51.659
-[pastor] Body of Christ.
-[person] Amen.

29:57.273 --> 30:00.711
-[pastor] Body of Christ.
-Body of Christ.

30:09.590 --> 30:10.939
-[pastor] Body of Christ.
-Body of Christ.

30:19.513 --> 30:21.776
-Body of Christ.
-Body of Christ.

30:26.520 --> 30:31.394
Madame. Please. Your glove.

30:31.525 --> 30:34.136
It is yours, surely.

30:34.223 --> 30:36.095
And now I see
it could not possibly be,

30:36.225 --> 30:37.792
for you have
quite a pair of your own.

30:37.923 --> 30:40.403
We are in God's house,
monsieur.

30:40.490 --> 30:42.014
I do not come here
to talk of gloves

30:42.101 --> 30:43.929
or other vanities
with strangers.

30:45.931 --> 30:47.497
Madame de Montrachet
wears only silk.

30:47.628 --> 30:49.369
Of course. My apologies.

30:49.456 --> 30:50.892
With skin so delicate,

30:50.979 --> 30:53.939
anything else would be
like grit to an oyster.

30:54.069 --> 30:56.811
[soft inquisitive music plays]

30:56.985 --> 31:00.423
♪ ♪

31:01.424 --> 31:04.514
Madame, before you leave,
I wanted to introduce myself.

31:04.645 --> 31:07.648
[laughter]

31:14.611 --> 31:16.265
[Azolan] If mademoiselle
loves you, sir,

31:16.352 --> 31:18.615
why would she set you
an impossible task?

31:18.746 --> 31:20.661
She cannot simply take me back.

31:20.748 --> 31:23.011
Her pride will not allow it.

31:25.013 --> 31:27.668
[suspenseful music plays]

31:27.842 --> 31:29.322
♪ ♪

31:29.452 --> 31:31.193
Bring me a paper and quill.

31:41.160 --> 31:45.338
"Camille, though perhaps
I should call you torturer,

31:45.468 --> 31:48.558
this task you have set me
is a fool's errand.

31:48.689 --> 31:50.560
I thought you sought
to punish me,

31:50.647 --> 31:53.433
because in that there is
the possibility of redemption.

31:53.520 --> 31:57.132
Now I see it is
my humiliation you desire.

31:57.263 --> 31:59.961
You may rest assured
this has been achieved.

32:00.092 --> 32:03.182
The only body that Jacqueline
de Montrachet desires

32:03.269 --> 32:05.488
is that of Christ.

32:05.619 --> 32:07.926
She is at the Saint-Sauveur
morning and night,

32:08.056 --> 32:09.753
praying to a God
who would not,

32:09.884 --> 32:14.236
I am sure,
condone this challenge.

32:14.367 --> 32:18.762
A more pious and pure woman
would be hard to find."

32:18.893 --> 32:22.549
Pious? Pious and pure?
She is neither.

32:34.909 --> 32:38.217
"So the great Valmont
has failed.

32:39.914 --> 32:41.568
Perhaps it is only
without my consent

32:41.655 --> 32:44.223
that you can seduce others.

32:44.353 --> 32:47.182
And I set you a task
suited to your skills,

32:47.313 --> 32:51.012
and you respond with defeat.

32:51.143 --> 32:53.493
I take from this that you do
not understand what it means

32:53.580 --> 32:55.538
for a woman
to give herself completely,

32:55.625 --> 32:57.366
or that you lied

32:57.497 --> 33:00.152
when you said would
do anything to win me back."

33:02.415 --> 33:04.199
[Victoire]
Should I wait for your reply?

33:06.767 --> 33:11.032
Valmont, lost for words?
Let's mark this day, Azolan.

33:12.642 --> 33:16.168
No more games.

33:16.255 --> 33:18.257
That is my reply.

33:18.344 --> 33:20.737
This is at an end.

33:20.868 --> 33:24.741
It's a message, I'm sure, even
with your limited vocabulary,

33:24.828 --> 33:26.265
you could relay without error.

33:29.920 --> 33:31.574
Good.

33:31.661 --> 33:33.794
Then you've let her down
for the last time.

33:36.405 --> 33:38.625
You have no idea
what you've done, do you?

33:40.409 --> 33:42.281
When you stole my letters,

33:42.411 --> 33:44.500
you didn't simply ruin things
between Camille and me.

33:44.631 --> 33:48.069
No, you set a fire burning
that will consume everyone

33:48.200 --> 33:50.854
and everything connected to it.

33:53.727 --> 33:54.989
Get out.

34:03.128 --> 34:06.000
Valmont does not decide
when this is over.

34:11.049 --> 34:12.702
-Monsieur.
-Hmm?

34:12.789 --> 34:14.617
-[Pascal grunts]
-[shocked cries]

34:14.748 --> 34:16.967
Stand up. Come with me.

34:18.839 --> 34:21.711
[tense music plays]

34:21.885 --> 34:25.193
♪ ♪

34:26.020 --> 34:28.414
I want these people gone
from here, now.

34:28.544 --> 34:30.111
[servant] Yes, monsieur.

34:46.954 --> 34:49.826
Mm.

34:49.913 --> 34:52.873
She has been in the water
some time.

34:53.003 --> 34:56.006
Perhaps from the night
she left to meet you.

34:56.137 --> 35:00.185
You betrayed Camille,
and so she drowned herself.

35:00.272 --> 35:02.796
How can you think
this is Camille?

35:02.926 --> 35:04.624
It does not suit you
to see the evidence

35:04.754 --> 35:07.583
of your immorality, monsieur?

35:07.714 --> 35:09.368
Look upon it.

35:13.285 --> 35:16.505
The proof. If it was needed.

35:22.642 --> 35:27.299
Have you no words of comfort
for her, monsieur?

35:27.429 --> 35:30.693
For the woman you ruined?

35:30.824 --> 35:32.826
May God have mercy on her soul.

35:36.221 --> 35:40.225
May God have mercy on yours.
As I will not.

35:40.399 --> 35:43.315
♪ ♪

36:17.566 --> 36:19.873
It's not possible, is it?
To summon the dead?

36:22.658 --> 36:25.052
It's the living here
I'm more afraid of.

36:25.183 --> 36:27.010
I found something.

36:27.097 --> 36:28.534
This isn't
the Majordome's writing.

36:28.664 --> 36:29.665
It's madame's.

36:29.752 --> 36:31.189
She says, "forgive me,"

36:31.276 --> 36:32.886
but what does
she need forgiveness for?

36:38.892 --> 36:40.981
[Camille] I have no time
for the riddles, Victoire.

36:41.111 --> 36:42.417
Just keep watch here
and make sense

36:42.548 --> 36:44.289
of what this contraption is.

36:44.376 --> 36:47.205
[Victoire] Where are you going?

36:47.292 --> 36:48.118
Where do you think?

36:48.293 --> 36:51.165
♪ ♪

36:54.995 --> 36:56.126
[knock at door]

37:03.046 --> 37:05.223
I don't want to fight.

37:05.353 --> 37:06.702
Neither do I.

37:18.323 --> 37:20.586
Why did you never
bring me here?

37:20.673 --> 37:22.849
It's hardly the house
I dreamed of for us.

37:24.807 --> 37:27.941
Perhaps if you had laid out
smaller dreams for us,

37:28.071 --> 37:30.335
the disappointment
would not be so great.

37:30.465 --> 37:33.120
I don't want
smaller dreams for us.

37:35.296 --> 37:37.342
I want to give you
another chance.

37:46.786 --> 37:49.528
To complete your task.

37:49.658 --> 37:52.008
You said you would do anything
to have me back.

37:52.139 --> 37:55.447
Jacqueline de Montrachet
is not for mortal man.

37:55.534 --> 37:57.927
Nor is she a damsel in distress
awaiting rescue.

38:00.147 --> 38:02.715
What's happened to you?

38:02.845 --> 38:04.586
If you love me, you'd protect
me as I protect you.

38:04.673 --> 38:06.327
I was not aware
of your protection.

38:06.458 --> 38:09.243
I mean, from your officer.
Gabriel Carré.

38:11.114 --> 38:12.986
How could you know him?

38:13.116 --> 38:14.988
[Pascal] He has a vendetta
against me because of you.

38:17.207 --> 38:18.165
Who is he?

38:21.734 --> 38:25.259
The sort of man that thought
I could be owned.

38:25.346 --> 38:27.087
Worse, because he believed
he was in love.

38:29.132 --> 38:31.134
Everything I'm running from.

38:31.265 --> 38:33.354
Well in your absence, he's
turned his attention against me.

38:33.441 --> 38:36.270
And it's already
cost me my job.

38:36.401 --> 38:37.880
Now he believes
he's found your body

38:38.011 --> 38:40.100
floating in the Seine.

38:40.230 --> 38:42.102
Drowned because
of my betrayal of you.

38:45.061 --> 38:46.324
What did you tell him?

38:49.675 --> 38:50.893
That it was you.

38:53.243 --> 38:56.377
Because every instinct in me
cries out

38:56.464 --> 39:00.468
that it's safer to be dead
to a man like that.

39:00.599 --> 39:02.252
Thank you.

39:03.950 --> 39:05.908
Are we even now, my love?

39:12.088 --> 39:15.048
When you have
made her love you.

39:15.135 --> 39:16.963
When you bring me proof.

39:22.577 --> 39:24.492
I know you will find a way.

39:24.623 --> 39:27.452
[inquisitive music plays]

39:27.626 --> 39:30.455
♪ ♪

39:45.600 --> 39:48.429
[laughter, indistinct chatter]

40:12.714 --> 40:14.063
What is it that you sell here?

40:14.150 --> 40:15.978
Settlements, sir.

40:16.109 --> 40:17.719
We have something for every man

40:17.850 --> 40:21.244
who has not the energy
to write his own.

40:21.331 --> 40:25.988
Activities, assumptions,
last judgments.

40:26.075 --> 40:27.860
Forgive us our trespasses.

40:27.947 --> 40:32.430
Passions, charity, sin,
and hell.

40:32.517 --> 40:34.475
Anything on hypocrisy?

40:43.702 --> 40:46.226
If one must trap a songbird...

40:49.011 --> 40:51.274
...one must first
learn its song.

40:56.628 --> 40:58.891
Tis a little brutal, Azolan.

41:01.459 --> 41:03.852
A pious man should show
no vanity.

41:03.983 --> 41:05.593
The change
will be good for you.

41:05.680 --> 41:07.073
I disagree.

41:07.160 --> 41:09.075
This crop
disbalances my features.

41:11.817 --> 41:13.775
I meant the lack
of vanity, sir.

41:23.263 --> 41:26.092
Ah. You have returned.

41:26.222 --> 41:27.920
Much like
my dead wife's spirit.

41:28.007 --> 41:30.009
Let's hear her truths.

41:35.318 --> 41:38.887
Have you forgotten
your reputation is in my hands?

41:39.018 --> 41:40.367
Geneva.

41:40.498 --> 41:44.197
Where you and madame
spent those springs.

41:44.284 --> 41:46.068
Do you really think
my wife would visit a city

41:46.155 --> 41:50.246
of infidels and revolution?

41:50.333 --> 41:53.598
Geneva is a house of care
on the way to Versailles,

41:53.685 --> 41:55.991
presided over by nuns
who would attempt to dispatch

41:56.122 --> 41:58.733
her melancholy
by bathing her in salts

41:58.864 --> 42:00.909
and letting out her blood.

42:01.040 --> 42:05.435
And each spring, like
the melancholy, she returned.

42:05.523 --> 42:08.613
[chuckles] Oh, come now.

42:08.743 --> 42:11.877
The Majordome, if he is
your spy, could not have known.

42:12.007 --> 42:15.315
Marriage must have
some secrets, hmm?

42:15.445 --> 42:17.447
No matter.

42:17.578 --> 42:19.145
Let the entertainment begin.

42:21.974 --> 42:25.194
Majordome, I need to see
the letter madame wrote.

42:25.325 --> 42:26.761
Please.

42:26.848 --> 42:27.762
Do you really think
you'll survive here

42:27.893 --> 42:29.416
if Camille doesn't?

42:34.943 --> 42:37.859
♪ ♪

42:42.560 --> 42:44.257
Put it back when you are done.

42:46.651 --> 42:48.827
Or it will be you
that won't survive here.

43:00.708 --> 43:02.971
[Victoire] "The bitter fruit
our marriage bore.

43:03.102 --> 43:05.321
"Apricot.

43:11.632 --> 43:12.894
"Ariadne.

43:23.035 --> 43:26.125
"Ariadne, forgive me.

43:26.212 --> 43:29.302
♪ ♪

43:37.484 --> 43:40.095
Does one bathe in it
or drink from it?

43:53.761 --> 43:55.720
I'm here, Lily.

43:58.200 --> 44:02.727
I understand that
I am to entertain you.

44:02.814 --> 44:05.077
That I should speak
to the dead on your behalf.

44:09.777 --> 44:12.040
It is true that between
this world and the next

44:12.127 --> 44:14.869
there is an invisible chain.

44:15.000 --> 44:16.958
I will not summon the dead.

44:19.091 --> 44:24.009
But this chain of fluid,

44:24.139 --> 44:26.315
this may draw the dead to us.

44:27.795 --> 44:29.318
Close your eyes.

44:41.156 --> 44:42.810
There is comfort on the dark.

44:47.815 --> 44:52.472
It is you, not me,
with power here.

44:52.602 --> 44:55.562
You need only be open
to what lies within.

44:55.693 --> 44:59.653
The magnetic sea
that draws knowledge

44:59.784 --> 45:01.873
and awakes what is hidden

45:01.960 --> 45:04.832
restores us to balance,
to health.

45:07.574 --> 45:09.141
Let me guide you, mistress.

45:13.232 --> 45:14.799
[whispering] It's Ariadne.

45:14.929 --> 45:16.452
The smudged word
from madame's notes.

45:16.583 --> 45:18.324
The same name
in the prayer books.

45:18.411 --> 45:20.979
It's someone they've wronged.
They are haunted by her.

45:24.852 --> 45:26.506
[mesmerist]
Let these magnetized waters

45:26.636 --> 45:30.815
connect and be guided
by the spirit within you.

45:30.945 --> 45:33.382
If you are willing to look,

45:33.513 --> 45:35.776
you will see
your own hearts tonight.

45:35.950 --> 45:38.779
♪ ♪

45:45.133 --> 45:47.788
I feel as if the rod draws me.

45:47.875 --> 45:51.096
I do not move, yet it--
yet it turns in my hands!

45:51.183 --> 45:53.794
[mesmerist]
We are portals to the past

45:53.881 --> 45:56.231
and to what is to come.

45:56.362 --> 45:58.625
Whether we choose
to listen or not.

46:06.851 --> 46:08.417
There is a great darkness
in this room.

46:10.202 --> 46:11.246
[gasps]

46:14.684 --> 46:16.599
Geneviève is here.

46:16.730 --> 46:17.992
I gave that vase to her
on her wedding.

46:18.123 --> 46:19.341
It is symbolic of her.

46:19.472 --> 46:20.516
It-it was me.
I knocked it over.

46:20.647 --> 46:24.216
Quiet! I see something.

46:24.346 --> 46:27.828
[gasps] I see her before me.

46:27.959 --> 46:31.353
In the water. Oh, she's crying.

46:31.440 --> 46:34.052
There is
an uninvited guest here.

46:34.182 --> 46:36.315
An imposter.

46:36.445 --> 46:39.622
A woman who makes her cry.

46:39.753 --> 46:41.276
She's saying
the same word over...

46:41.407 --> 46:42.669
-Liar.
-[Christine] And over again.

46:42.800 --> 46:44.540
-She is saying--
-"Ariadne!"

46:47.326 --> 46:49.632
She's saying, "Ariadne."

46:49.763 --> 46:53.985
She's saying, "Forgive me."

46:54.115 --> 46:56.378
she wants to talk.

46:56.465 --> 46:57.858
She wants to talk of Ariadne.

46:57.989 --> 47:00.339
-Be silent. Be silent.
-Let go.

47:00.469 --> 47:03.385
[tense music plays]

47:03.559 --> 47:06.258
♪ ♪

47:07.868 --> 47:09.304
[screams]

47:29.977 --> 47:34.329
Victoire. Victoire!

47:34.416 --> 47:36.592
Say something.
Majordome! Majordome!

47:40.553 --> 47:42.598
Victoire.

47:42.685 --> 47:45.906
Charlatan. Fraud.

47:46.037 --> 47:47.908
I promised you a mirror.

47:47.995 --> 47:49.736
I did not promise
you would like what you saw.

47:49.823 --> 47:51.172
Get out of my house!

47:51.259 --> 47:52.391
Once the child is safe.

47:52.478 --> 47:54.219
Get out!

48:00.747 --> 48:02.053
[mesmerist]
It is an intuition of sorts,

48:02.140 --> 48:03.924
the falling sickness.

48:04.011 --> 48:05.186
You should note when she falls.

48:05.273 --> 48:07.275
Events before may be symbolic.

48:07.362 --> 48:09.364
[Camille] Like your intuition.

48:09.495 --> 48:11.714
You didn't hold a mirror
up to anyone.

48:11.801 --> 48:16.371
I made it up.
Now, please leave us.

48:16.502 --> 48:20.549
You are in great pain
from a past wound.

48:20.680 --> 48:24.684
A wrong done to you.
A betrayal of trust.

48:24.814 --> 48:26.033
I am in pain.

48:29.515 --> 48:31.647
What have you seen?

48:31.734 --> 48:34.737
The damage done to you.

48:34.824 --> 48:37.305
But now you must forgive.

48:37.392 --> 48:41.266
Only through forgiveness
can you find the light.

48:41.396 --> 48:44.617
-I must forgive?
-To find the light.

48:44.747 --> 48:49.230
Otherwise, the darkness here
will overtake you.

48:49.317 --> 48:52.016
Then you have seen
nothing of my pain.

48:53.713 --> 48:56.890
For I cannot forgive.

48:57.021 --> 48:59.240
And I don't want the light,
monsieur.

48:59.371 --> 49:02.200
[suspenseful music plays]

49:02.374 --> 49:05.377
♪ ♪

49:16.997 --> 49:20.261
And it is through the meek,

49:20.392 --> 49:22.350
through the poor,

49:22.437 --> 49:25.353
that we shall truly know God.

49:25.484 --> 49:29.227
The Lord cares not for riches.

49:29.314 --> 49:32.404
The Lord cares only
for the heart.

49:32.534 --> 49:33.622
God be with you.

49:33.753 --> 49:34.928
[all] And with you.

49:42.022 --> 49:43.632
Father.

49:43.719 --> 49:45.721
Forgive me,
but I am new to this church,

49:45.808 --> 49:48.942
and I was moved by your words.

49:49.073 --> 49:50.857
The other morning, I watched a
young boy

49:50.988 --> 49:53.381
eat half an egg
for his breakfast.

49:53.512 --> 49:56.689
So little had he,
that to him, this was a feast.

49:56.819 --> 49:58.517
It broke my heart.

49:58.647 --> 50:01.607
[pastor] The Church
does all it can, monsieur.

50:07.091 --> 50:10.311
[indistinct chatter]

50:10.398 --> 50:12.618
[Pascal] But what of the rich?

50:12.705 --> 50:14.359
Where is their love
for the children?

50:14.489 --> 50:17.014
Starving in orphanages
on the streets?

50:17.144 --> 50:19.929
Surely, God would not condone
such hypocrisy.

50:20.060 --> 50:23.020
We have lost our morality,
and without it, we are adrift.

50:23.107 --> 50:25.370
I do not know how
I can help you, my child.

50:25.457 --> 50:27.807
[Pascal] It is I who offers
myself to you.

50:27.937 --> 50:30.331
To the Church.

50:30.462 --> 50:33.465
It is I who will do
all I can to help you.

50:33.552 --> 50:34.857
Help the children.

50:39.079 --> 50:42.604
-What is your name, sir?
-Monsieur Lucien, madame.

50:42.735 --> 50:44.215
And yours?

50:44.345 --> 50:45.564
Madame de Montrachet.

50:49.220 --> 50:52.049
I was moved by your words.

50:52.179 --> 50:54.964
It's rare for a man
to speak from the heart.

50:55.052 --> 50:57.663
[Pascal] It was no more
than needed to be said.

50:57.793 --> 50:59.926
Yet it was previously unsaid.

51:00.013 --> 51:02.972
♪ ♪

51:08.543 --> 51:10.545
[Jacqueline]
You have brought such shame.

51:10.676 --> 51:14.245
[Camille] Madame, please.
I'm sorry. I'm sorry.

51:14.375 --> 51:15.811
[Jacqueline]
Sorry for your lies?

51:15.898 --> 51:17.639
For all the damage
you've done here?

51:17.770 --> 51:21.600
I'm sorry for it all.
Forgive me.

51:23.732 --> 51:26.083
Even God doesn't forgive.

51:26.213 --> 51:29.042
[tense music plays]

51:29.216 --> 51:32.089
♪ ♪

51:46.277 --> 51:48.496
Even God does not forgive.

51:48.670 --> 51:51.586
♪ ♪

52:18.265 --> 52:21.050
[dramatic string music plays]

52:21.138 --> 52:24.053
♪ ♪
